  "text": "Resistance to gastric acidity, hydrolysis by mammalian enzymes, and gastrointestinal absorption. The resistance of inulin to digestive processes has been extensively studied by applying all the methods (both in vitro and in vivo) described in the section Testing Methodologies. Inulin is a nondigestible oligosaccharide that, for nutritional labeling, classifies as dietary fiber [CITATION_1] .",
